reviewText: After the thrill of seeing Halloween 6 in Blu Ray, and giving this a 5 Star review... I've come back to it a few times over the past year or so... I'm knocking it down to 3 Stars.Seeing Halloween 6 is lots of fun no doubt, and it doesn't look too terrible... I mean it's Halloween 6, I didn't expect them to totally go through and perfect each and every second of the transfer... It's not like Spielberg or Lucas is overseeing the transfer... lol.H20 looks horrid. Plain and simple, it's a dark transfer... I've even turned the brightness up on my TV to try and adjust, but it just isn't happening.The sound is only 2.0. Halloween Resurrection, which is my least favorite Halloween movie BY FAR, sounds so much better on Blu Ray than this release. If they could give Halloween Resurrection 5.0 sound, why couldn't they do it with this release? The sound isn't horrible, but the missing surround sound is noticeable.Fact is I still enjoy watching H6 on Blu Ray... It fares much better than H20... And this package ends up costing about $6 per movie.. Can't beat that... But H20 could look much better, and the 2.0 sound is a huge downfall.

reviewText: I picked this up at Walmart today for $5, for the price it was a good deal. I have read everything negative about H20's transfer to Blu, so I will check it out. So far Halloween 6 looks pretty decent. For $5, even if H20 looks terrible, it isn't a huge waste of money.(CONCLUSION)OK, so lastnight I watched Halloween 6 and today I watched H20. What are people complaining about? H6 looks pretty good, and H20 may be dark in some spots, but I think it looks pretty decent. I am glad I made my own decision because each of these films looks pretty good. Better than they have. So for the price, I say it's not a bad deal. B-
